ðŸ§  What is this?
In JavaScript, this refers to the object that is calling the function.

It can change depending on how the function is called â€” not where it's defined.

ðŸ§  Summary Table

| Call Style                                | `this` refers to                     |
| ----------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `obj.method()`                            | The object                           |
| Regular function (non-strict)             | `window` (global)                    |
| Regular function (strict)                 | `undefined`                          |
| Arrow function                            | Lexical scope (where it was defined) |
| Detached method (`const fn = obj.method`) | `undefined` / `window`               |
| Bound function (`.bind(obj)`)             | The bound object                     |
| DOM event listener (regular)              | The element                          |
| DOM event listener (arrow)                | Outer scope                          |
